<title>GERMANY: Lufthansa adds UK capacity amid BA strikes.</title>
<headline>Lufthansa adds UK capacity amid BA strikes.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1997-07-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>German airline Deutsche Lufthansa AG said on Tuesday it planned to add extra capacity and flights to Britain to accommodate passengers facing problems because of an impending strike by British Airways Plc cabin staff.</p>
<p>Lufthansa said that larger aircraft and additional flights would form the basis of the extra capacity, which would be added to London-Hamburg, London-Frankfurt, and London-Berlin routes.</p>
<p>British Airways cabin crew are currently planning a 72-hour strike, due to start at 0500 GMT on Wednesday, which may strand thousands of tourists and business travellers. BA said on Tuesday the strike looked almost certain to go ahead.</p>
<p>-- Kate Kelland, Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
